`lux`: a High Performance Computing Framework
=============================================

`lux` is a framework for developing portable high performance
scientific computing software on distributed heterogeneous systems.

Based on a generic performance model, `lux` provides resource and task
abstractions to support runtime optimization.  It manages resource,
measures task performance, and then dynamically adjusts the algorithms
to achieve portable performance for distributed heterogeneous systems.

Using a simple module architecture, `lux` provides basic functions to
access modules/plug-ins and supports configuring, planning, and
running scientific computing jobs.  Almost everything in `lux` is
implemented as a module.  This makes `lux` lightweight but powerful.
